      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>The Acts of St George. According to the copied colophon, the author of the text,
               whose name is <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13151Saqrates">Pasicrates (Saqrāṭǝs)</persName>, the
               servant of St George, finished this work while they were travelling in the country of
               Constantinople to a place called “Qʷǝsqʷās Mars”, where St George’s martyrdom took
               place on the 23th of Miyāzyā (<bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/JCCVEYK8"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1930George"/><title level="m">George of Lydda, the Patron Saint of England: A Study of the Cultus of St. George in Ethiopia. The Ethiopic texts in facsimile edited for the first time from the manuscripts from Maḳdalâ now in the British Museum, with translations and an introduction</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest A. Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Co. Ltd.</publisher><date>1930</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">20</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">20</biblScope><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/stgeorge_20190327</note><citedRange>274-275</citedRange></bibl>). The note states that the text was
               translated from Arabic into Gǝʿǝz by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7077Mikael">Michael “the
                  younger”</persName>, the grandson of ʾabbā George, son of ʾabbā Michael the Bishop
                     (<bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/JCCVEYK8"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1930George"/><title level="m">George of Lydda, the Patron Saint of England: A Study of the Cultus of St. George in Ethiopia. The Ethiopic texts in facsimile edited for the first time from the manuscripts from Maḳdalâ now in the British Museum, with translations and an introduction</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest A. Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Co. Ltd.</publisher><date>1930</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">20</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">20</biblScope><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/stgeorge_20190327</note><citedRange>275</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
