               <listBibl type="editions">
                  <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/99CSH8ZD"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:1967GadlaGiyorgis"/><title level="m">ገድለ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ በግዕዝና፡ በአማርኛ (Gadla Giyorgis ba-Gǝʿzǝnnā ʾAmārǝññā, The Life of George: Geez and Amharic)</title><pubPlace>ʾAddis ʾAbabā</pubPlace><publisher>Bǝrhānǝnnā Salām Hāyla Śǝllase I Māttamiyā Bet</publisher><date>1967</date><citedRange unit="page">21–83</citedRange><citedRange unit="chapter">3–9</citedRange></bibl>
               </listBibl>
               
               <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit">
                  <ab> ገድል፡ ወስምዕ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ወብፁዕ፡ ሰማዕት፡ ዐቢይ፡ ማር፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ዘፈጸመ፡ ገድሎ፡
                     አመ፡ ፪ወ፫፡ ለወርኃ፡ መርሙደ፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ሚያዝያ።</ab>
                  <note>
                     <listBibl type="editions">
                        <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/99CSH8ZD"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:1967GadlaGiyorgis"/><title level="m">ገድለ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ በግዕዝና፡ በአማርኛ (Gadla Giyorgis ba-Gǝʿzǝnnā ʾAmārǝññā, The Life of George: Geez and Amharic)</title><pubPlace>ʾAddis ʾAbabā</pubPlace><publisher>Bǝrhānǝnnā Salām Hāyla Śǝllase I Māttamiyā Bet</publisher><date>1967</date><citedRange unit="page">21</citedRange><citedRange unit="chapter">3.1</citedRange></bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                  </note>
               </div>
            </div>
            
            <div type="textpart" subtype="colophon" xml:id="coloph1">
               <ab>ወሶበ፡ ፈጸመ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ገድሎ፡ አነ፡ ሰቅራጥስ፡ ገብሩ፡ ለጊዮርጊስ፡ ኮንኩ፡ እትልዎ፡ ለእግዚእየ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ በኵሉ፡
                     <add place="above">ገድሉ፡</add> ወፃማሁ፡ ወለካልሁ፡ ዘንተ፡ ጸሐፍኩ፡<gap reason="ellipsis"/>
                  ተፈጸመ፡ እንዘ፡ ንነግድ፡ ብሔረ፡ ቈስጠንጢኖስ፡ መካን፡ ዘስሙ፡ ቍስቋስ፡ መርስ፡ እንዘ፡ ንነግድ፡ ወአስተዳሎኩ፡ ዘንተ፡ መጽሐፈ።
                  ወኮነ፡ በዘአዕረፈ፡ እግዚእየ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ሃብሩ፡ ለኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ በዘተከለለ፡ ወርኁ፡ በጽርዕ፡ ጵንፍልዮ፡ ስሙ፡
                  ወትርጓሜሁ፡ ወርኃ፡ ሚያዝያ፡ አመ፡ ፳ወ፫ለሠርቅ፡ ወዕለቱሂ፡ ዓርብ፡ በጊዜ፡ ፱ሰዓት፡ አሜን። ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ ተተርጐመት፡ ዛቲ፡
                  መጽሐፍ፡ አምሳነ፡ ዓረቢ፡ በግዕዝ፡ በአፈ፡ ሚካኤል፡ {ዘይንዕስ} ፡ ወልደ፡ ወልዱ፡ ለአባ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወልደ፡ አባ፡ ሚካኤል፡
                  ጳጳስ። <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን፡</ab>
               <note>quoted after <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESaqg014">Gulo Maḵadā, ʿĀddi Qolqʷāl Giyorgis, AQG-014</ref>, same in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/JCCVEYK8"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1930George"/><title level="m">George of Lydda, the Patron Saint of England: A Study of the Cultus of St. George in Ethiopia. The Ethiopic texts in facsimile edited for the first time from the manuscripts from Maḳdalâ now in the British Museum, with translations and an introduction</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest A. Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Co. Ltd.</publisher><date>1930</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">20</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">20</biblScope><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/stgeorge_20190327</note><citedRange>274–276</citedRange></bibl>
                  <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/99CSH8ZD"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:1967GadlaGiyorgis"/><title level="m">ገድለ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ በግዕዝና፡ በአማርኛ (Gadla Giyorgis ba-Gǝʿzǝnnā ʾAmārǝññā, The Life of George: Geez and Amharic)</title><pubPlace>ʾAddis ʾAbabā</pubPlace><publisher>Bǝrhānǝnnā Salām Hāyla Śǝllase I Māttamiyā Bet</publisher><date>1967</date><citedRange unit="page">83</citedRange><citedRange unit="chapter">9.23</citedRange></bibl>
                  <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/A2CZ8F67"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:1968GadTamMalkGiyorgis"/><title level="m">ገድለ ጊዮርጊስ ወተአምራቲሁ ዘምስለ መልክአ ጊዮርጊስ። (Gadla giyorgis wataʾammǝrātihu zamǝsla malkǝʿa giyorgis, 'The Life of George and His Miracles Together with the Effigy of George')</title><pubPlace>ʾAddis ʾAbabā</pubPlace><publisher>Tasfā Māttamiyā Bet</publisher><date>1968</date><citedRange unit="page">119–120</citedRange><citedRange unit="chapter">9</citedRange></bibl>
               </note>
            </div>
            
            <div type="textpart" subtype="colophon" xml:id="coloph2">
               <ab>ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ ተተርጐመት፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ እምልሳነ፡ ዐረቢ፡ ለግዕዝ፡ በአፈ፡ <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7077Mikael">ሚካኤል፡</persName> ዘይንስ፡ ወልደ፡ ወልዱ፡ ለ<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12753Giyorgis"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title">አባ፡</t:roleName>ጊዮርጊስ፡</persName> ወልደ፡ አባ፡ <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12754Mikale"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="title">አባ፡</t:roleName> ሚካኤል፡</persName>
                  ጳጳስ፡ እንዘ፡ ይረድኦ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ።</ab>
               <note>Copied colophon of the translation, taken from <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient712">London, British Library, BL Oriental 712</ref></note>
               <div type="textpart" subtype="colophon" xml:id="coloph3">
                 <ab>ወፍዳሜሁሰ፡ ኮነ፡ ፪ለወርኋ፡ ታስሪን፡ ቀደማይ፡ በሐሳቦሙ፡ ለዕብራውያን፡ ወበግዕዝ፡ አመ፡ ፬ለጥቅምተ፡ በሓሳበ፡ ፅሐይ፡ ወበሣልስ፡ ኆንት፡ በጊዜ፡ ግብአቱ፡ አምራብዕ፡ በ፱ዓውድ፡ ቀመር፡ በ፩ጥንትዮን፡ 
                 ወበ፬ዓውደ፡ ዕለት። በ፱አበቅቴ፡ በካልአ፡ ዓመተ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ለደዊት፡ ንጉሠ፡ አግዓዜ፡ ወልደ፡ ናዖድ፡ ንጉሠ፡ ርቱዓ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ 
                 በዕለተ፡ ሰኑይ፡ በ፲ሰዓት፡ ዘመዓልት፡ አመ፡ ከርመ፡ በምድረ፡ አዘዞ።</ab>
                   <note>The copied colophon (taken from <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient713">London, British Library, BL Oriental 713</ref>) gives the precise date of translation, 
                     <date when="1510">2nd year of the reign of Dawit (that is, Lǝbna Dǝngǝl), who began his reign in August 1508</date> </note>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
